</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,222,318]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<bibRefCitation author="Lever" box="[151,315,222,246]" pageId="15" pageNumber="17" refString="Lever, R. J. A. W. (1945 a) An annotated checklist of the mealybugs and scale insects of Fiji. Agricultural Journal, Department of Agriculture, Fiji, 16, 41 - 44." type="journal article" year="1945" yearSuffix="a">
Lever (
<number box="[236,294,222,246]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1945.0">1945</number>
a)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Hinckley" box="[379,568,222,246]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Hinckley, A. D. (1965) Trophic records of some insects, mites and ticks in Fiji. Department of Agriculture, Fiji, No. 45, 1 - 116." type="book chapter" year="1965">
Hinckley (
<number box="[502,560,222,246]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1965.0">1965</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
recorded 
<taxonomicName authority="Cockerell" authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1868" box="[691,1125,222,246]" class="Insecta" family="Asterolecaniidae" genus="Asterolecanium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pustulans">
<emphasis box="[691,985,222,246]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Asterolecanium pustulans</emphasis>
(Cockerell)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1202,1241,222,246]" name="Fiji" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fiji</collectingCountry>
on bamboo and 
<taxonomicName box="[151,480,259,283]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Schizostachyum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glaucifolium">
<emphasis box="[151,480,259,283]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Schizostachyum glaucifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. These records were found to be misidentifications for 
<taxonomicName box="[1120,1238,259,283]" class="Insecta" family="Asterolecaniidae" genus="Bambusaspis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robusta">
<emphasis box="[1120,1238,259,283]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">B. robusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Williams" pageId="15" pageNumber="17" refString="Williams, D. J. &amp; Watson, G. W. (1990) The Scale Insects of the Tropical South Pacific Region. Pt. 3. The Soft Scales (Coccidae) and other families. CAB International Institute of Entomology, London. 267 pp." type="book" year="1990">
Williams and Watson (
<number box="[249,310,294,318]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1990.0">1990</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. The present specimens were collected on Taveuni, Bouma, on leaves of 
<taxonomicName box="[1137,1241,294,318]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Bambusa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1137,1241,294,318]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Bambusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp., 
<date box="[1294,1425,294,318]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="2009-07-23">
<number box="[1294,1323,294,318]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="23.0">23</number>
.vii. 
<number box="[1363,1425,294,318]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="2009.0">2009</number>
</date>
.
</paragraph>
